🔤 Power Apps Text Functions & Definitions:
-------------------------------------------
Text() – Converts numbers, dates, and times into a text format. ━━━━━ Example: Text(Today(), "dd-mm-yyyy")

Concatenate() – Combines multiple text strings into together.  ━━━━━ Example: Concatenate("Hello ", "World")

& (Ampersand) – Shortcut to join text values. ━━━━━ Example: "First" & "Name"

Left() – Returns a specified number of characters from the start of a string. ━━━━━ Example: Left("PowerApps", 5) → "Power"

Right() – Returns characters from the end of a string.   ━━━━━ Example: Right("PowerApps", 4) → "Apps"

Mid() – Returns a substring from the middle of a string. ━━━━━ Example: Mid("PowerApps", 6, 4) → "Apps"

Len() – Returns the number of characters in a string.    ━━━━━  Example: Len("PowerApps") → 9

Upper() – Converts all text to uppercase. ━━━━━ Example: Upper("hello") → "HELLO"

Lower() – Converts all text to lowercase. ━━━━━ Example: Lower("HELLO") → "hello"

Trim() – Removes spaces from the beginning and end of a string. ━━━━━  Example: Trim(" Hello ") → "Hello"

Substitute() – Replaces part of a string with another string.   ━━━━━ Example: Substitute("Power Apps", " ", "") → "PowerApps"

Find() – Returns the position of a substring within a string (case-sensitive). ━━━━━ Example: Find("A", "PowerApps") → 6























